at his firing had anything to do with being an outspoken Trump supporter wh=
o protested the company=E2=80=99s vaccine mandate. The judge just didn=E2=
=80=99t see sufficient evidence at the time that the termination was politi=
cally motivated. Disney argued successfully that the vaccine mandate was a =
rational necessity to protect unvaccinated, unmasked workers.

Just yesterday, however, Goorvitch told the parties that he was inclined to=
 vacate his own judgment after Street brought attention to a deposition in =
the Dunbar case in which an in-house Disney attorney admitted to denying an=
 accommodation because the =E2=80=9Cstated reason was political, not religi=
ous.=E2=80=9D Goorvitch seemed particularly swayed by news that Disney rehi=
red another General Hospital star, Steve Burton, who had also refused to
get vaccinated but wasn=E2=80=99t outspoken about his politics. As a result=
, Disney could be facing a trial in the Rademacher case, too.

Either way, plaintiffs like Dunbar and Rademacher won=E2=80=99t be the last=
=2E Sooner or later, we=E2=80=99re likely=20=
to see Disney portray itself to jur=
ors as a beneficent employer enforcing reasonable, union-negotiated safety =
protocols to protect its workforce. After all, while the Dunbar and Rademac=
her suits are nominally about vaccine
mandates, they also belong to a bigger bucket of litigation exploring how H=
ollywood tackles divisive topics such as diversity and health. The Elon Mus=
k-funded Gina Carano case ( https://puck.news/assessing-the-elon-musk-gina-=
carano-case-against-disney/?utm_campaign=3DWhat+I%27m+Hearing%2B+-+SUBSCRIB=
ERS+%282%2F11%2F25%29&utm_content=3DWhat+I%27m+Hearing%2B+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%28=
2%2F11%2F25%29&utm_medium=3Demail_action&utm_source=3Dcustomer.io&utm_term=
=3Df6c60617da42abd12a ) against Disney, over her firing from The Mandaloria=
n, is another example.=C2=A0

Of course, I=E2=80=99m sure Disney C.E.O.
Bob Iger would prefer to steer clear of contentious political debates, as e=
videnced by the company=E2=80=99s new efforts ( https://www.axios.com/2025/=
02/11/disney-dei-changes-trump-era?stream=3Dtop&utm_source=3Dalert&utm_medi=
um=3Demail&utm_campaign=3Dalerts_media_trends&utm_campaign=3DWhat+I%27m+Hea=
ring%2B+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%282%2F11%2F25%29&utm_content=3DWhat+I%27m+Hearing%2B=
+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%282%2F11%2F25%29&utm_medium=3Demail_action&utm_source=3Dcus=
tomer.io&utm_term=3Df6c60617da42abd12a ) to shift away from its D.E.I. prog=
rams, but over the next four years, they seem unavoidable. In the Dunbar ca=
se, Street originally teamed with Robert F.
Kennedy Jr., a fellow attorney at JW Howard who is now more focused on join=
ing the Trump administration. Kennedy, obviously, is no longer involved in =
the litigation against Disney, although one shouldn=E2=80=99t discount the =
possibility that he directs health agencies to submit amicus briefs after h=
is likely confirmation as America=E2=80=99s top health official this week.

